cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper deals with the problem of designing a measurement operator and a reconstruction/inference network that can operate over a range of measurement rates. This problem is relevant to several computer vision and machine learning tasks, such as object tracking and image recognition. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel training algorithm for learning rate-adaptive networks, which involves optimizing a joint objective function. This aspect of the paper is relevant to the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the use of spatial multiplexing cameras, which involves compressive sensing techniques, and the design of measurement operators, which involves information theory. Therefore, the sub-categories cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.MM (Multimedia) are also likely.
